<title>
Gear Shift and Select Shaft Assembly Disassembly and Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206012">Gear Shift and Select Shaft Assembly Removal and Installation</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A5206011">Gear Shift and Select Shaft Assembly Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Disassemble and reassemble gear shift and select shaft assembly while referring to the following precautions and figure.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Push spring pins out using special tool below.
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L5B006">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09925-78210">
09925–78210
</s-number>
<ptxt>
6.0 mm
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Inspect component parts for wear, distortion or damage. If any defect is found, replace defective part with new one.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
The gear shift and select shaft may be bent if the spring pins are driven without using any support on the back of the spring pin fitting location.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Be sure to support the spring pin fitting location from behind with a wooden block when installing the spring pins.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
